<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>{{ report_name }}</title>
{#- ── helpers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -#}
{%- set S = {} -%}
{%- for s in sections %}{% set _ = S.update({s.key: s}) %}{% endfor -%}
{%- set O = (S.overview.data[0] if S.overview and S.overview.data else {}) -%}
{%- set SEC = S.by_sector.data if S.by_sector else [] -%}
{%- set PRS = S.pressure.data if S.pressure else [] -%}
{%- set AP  = S.ap_lines.data if S.ap_lines else [] -%}
{%- set GRN = S.grn_lines.data if S.grn_lines else [] -%}
{%- set PO  = S.open_po.data if S.open_po else [] -%}
{%- set PR  = S.open_pr.data if S.open_pr else [] -%}
{%- macro money(v) -%}
  {%- if v is none %}&mdash;
  {%- elif v|abs >= 1000000000 %}{{ (v/1000000000)|round(2)|fmt }}&nbsp;B
  {%- elif v|abs >= 1000000 %}{{ (v/1000000)|round(1)|fmt }}&nbsp;M
  {%- elif v|abs >= 1000 %}{{ (v/1000)|round(0)|int|fmt }}&nbsp;K
  {%- else %}{{ v|round(0)|int|fmt }}{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}
{%- macro dt(v) -%}{%- if v %}{{ v.strftime('%Y-%m-%d') if v.strftime is defined else v }}{% else %}&mdash;{% endif -%}{%- endmacro -%}
<style>
  :root { --brand: {{ brand|default('#1F6F8B') }}; --brand-d: #17596F; --gold: #B58900;
          --enc: #C25E10; --ok: #1E7B4D; --bad: #B3352B; --ink: #1F2933; --mut: #7B8794; }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: "Segoe UI", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif; color: var(--ink);
         margin: 0; font-size: 10px; }
  @page { size: A4 landscape; }
  .page { page-break-after: always; }
  .page:last-child { page-break-after: auto; }

  /* ── cover ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .cover { height: 172mm; position: relative; overflow: hidden;
           background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFFFFF 55%, #F0F5F7 100%); }
  .cv-band { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 14mm;
             background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--brand-d), var(--brand) 60%, #3E93AF); }
  .cv-band2 { position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 6mm;
              background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--gold), var(--enc)); }
  .cv-org { margin: 26mm 0 0 18mm; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: .22em;
            text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--mut); }
  .cv-title { margin: 6mm 0 0 18mm; font-size: 46px; line-height: 1.08; font-weight: 800;
              color: var(--brand-d); }
  .cv-sub { margin: 4mm 0 0 18mm; font-size: 18px; color: var(--gold); font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: .04em; }
  .cv-scope { margin: 10mm 0 0 18mm; display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; max-width: 200mm; }
  .cv-scope span { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #D3E0E5; border-left: 4px solid var(--brand);
                   border-radius: 3px; padding: 5px 12px; font-size: 11px; color: #33525E; }
  .cv-scope b { color: var(--brand-d); }
  .cv-desc { margin: 8mm 0 0 18mm; max-width: 150mm; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.65;
             color: #52606D; }
  .cv-prep { position: absolute; bottom: 12mm; left: 18mm; font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--mut); }
  .cv-prep b { display: block; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--brand-d); margin-top: 2px; }
  .cv-prep i { display: block; font-style: normal; color: #52606D; margin-top: 1px; }
  .cv-date { position: absolute; bottom: 12mm; right: 18mm; text-align: right;
             font-size: 10px; color: var(--mut); }
  .cv-date b { display: block; font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink); }

  /* ── table of contents ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .toc-h { border-bottom: 3px solid var(--brand); padding-bottom: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .toc-h h2 { margin: 0; font-size: 22px; color: var(--brand-d); }
  .toc { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; }
  .toc td { padding: 9px 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid #E4E7EB; vertical-align: top; }
  .toc .no { width: 52px; font-size: 17px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--brand);
             font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .toc .t { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); }
  .toc .d { font-size: 10px; color: var(--mut); margin-top: 2px; }
  .toc .n { width: 130px; text-align: right; font-size: 10px; color: #52606D;
            font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; white-space: nowrap; }

  /* ── part banner + section furniture ───────────────────────────────── */
  .pt-band { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; background:
             linear-gradient(90deg, var(--brand-d), var(--brand)); color: #fff;
             border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 14px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .pt-no { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 800; opacity: .85; }
  .pt-t { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; }
  .pt-s { margin-left: auto; font-size: 9.5px; opacity: .85; text-align: right; }
  .sub-h { border-left: 4px solid var(--brand); background: #F0F5F7; padding: 4px 8px;
           font-size: 11.5px; font-weight: 700; color: #24404B; margin: 12px 0 6px; }
  .sub-h small { font-weight: 400; color: var(--mut); }

  /* ── KPI tiles ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .kpis { display: flex; gap: 7px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .kpi { flex: 1 1 100px; border: 1px solid #D8E2E7; border-top: 3px solid var(--brand);
         border-radius: 4px; padding: 6px 9px; background: #FBFDFE; }
  .kpi.k-act { border-top-color: var(--gold); }
  .kpi.k-enc { border-top-color: var(--enc); }
  .kpi.k-ok { border-top-color: var(--ok); }
  .kpi.k-bad { border-top-color: var(--bad); }
  .k-lbl { font-size: 8px; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--mut); }
  .k-val { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; margin-top: 1px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .k-sub { font-size: 8.5px; color: var(--mut); margin-top: 1px; }
  .neg { color: var(--bad); }

  /* ── charts (pure CSS/HTML — deterministic in print) ───────────────── */
  .charts { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .chart { flex: 1 1 0; border: 1px solid #E0E8EC; border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 10px;
           background: #fff; }
  .ch-t { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; color: #24404B; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .hb-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; margin: 3px 0; }
  .hb-lbl { flex: 0 0 118px; font-size: 8.5px; color: #3E4C59; text-align: right;
            white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }
  .hb-track { flex: 1 1 0; background: #EEF2F5; border-radius: 2px; height: 9px; }
  .hb-bar { height: 9px; border-radius: 2px; background: var(--brand); min-width: 1px; }
  .hb-bar.warn { background: var(--enc); } .hb-bar.bad { background: var(--bad); }
  .hb-bar.gold { background: var(--gold); } .hb-bar.ok { background: var(--ok); }
  .hb-val { flex: 0 0 64px; font-size: 8.5px; color: #33525E; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
            white-space: nowrap; }
  /* stacked composition bar */
  .stack { display: flex; height: 20px; border-radius: 3px; overflow: hidden; margin: 4px 0 6px; }
  .stack div { height: 20px; }
  .lg { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; font-size: 8.5px; color: #3E4C59; }
  .lg i { display: inline-block; width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 2px; margin-right: 4px; }
  /* monthly column chart */
  .cols { display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 8px; height: 110px; padding-top: 4px; }
  .col-g { flex: 1 1 0; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 2px; height: 100px;
           border-bottom: 2px solid #CBD2D9; }
  .col-g div { flex: 1 1 0; border-radius: 2px 2px 0 0; }
  .col-ap { background: var(--brand); } .col-grn { background: var(--gold); }
  .col-lbl { font-size: 7.5px; color: var(--mut); text-align: center; margin-top: 3px; }

  /* ── data tables ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  table.data { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; }
  table.data thead th { background: var(--brand); color: #fff; font-weight: 600; text-align: left;
                        padding: 4px 6px; font-size: 8.5px; border: 1px solid var(--brand-d); }
  table.data tbody td { padding: 3px 6px; border: 1px solid #E4E7EB; vertical-align: top;
                        font-size: 8.5px; }
  table.data tbody tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #F5F7FA; }
  td.num, tfoot td.num { text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; white-space: nowrap; }
  table.data tfoot td { padding: 4px 6px; border: 1px solid #CBD2D9; background: #E3ECEF;
                        font-weight: 700; color: #24404B; font-size: 8.5px; }
  .empty { padding: 16px; text-align: center; color: var(--mut); font-style: italic;
           border: 1px dashed #D3DCE2; }
  .pill { display: inline-block; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0 6px; font-size: 8px; }
  .pill.paid { background: #E1F3E8; color: var(--ok); }
  .pill.part { background: #FCF0DE; color: #8A5E00; }
  .pill.unp  { background: #FBE4E1; color: var(--bad); }

  /* ── insights ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .ins { border: 1px solid #E0E8EC; border-left: 4px solid var(--brand); border-radius: 4px;
         background: #FBFDFE; padding: 9px 12px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .ins .i-t { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--brand-d); margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .ins .i-b { font-size: 10px; line-height: 1.55; color: #3E4C59; }
  .ins b { color: var(--ink); }
  .meth { margin-top: 12px; border: 1px dashed #C9D6DC; border-radius: 4px; padding: 9px 12px;
          background: #F7FAFB; }
  .meth h4 { margin: 0 0 5px; font-size: 10px; color: var(--brand-d); text-transform: uppercase;
             letter-spacing: .08em; }
  .meth div { font-size: 9px; color: #52606D; line-height: 1.6; }
  .meth b { color: #33525E; }
  .foot { margin-top: 10px; font-size: 8px; color: #9AA5B1; text-align: center; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

{#- ═══ COVER ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -#}
<div class="page cover">
  <div class="cv-band"></div>
  <div class="cv-org">i-Finance &middot; Reporting Platform</div>
  <div class="cv-title">Budget Utilization<br>Briefing Book</div>
  <div class="cv-sub">Budget Year {{ params.year }}</div>
  <div class="cv-scope">
    <span>Scope <b>{{ params.sector if params.sector else 'All sectors' }}</b></span>
    {% if params.projecttype %}<span>Project type <b>{{ params.projecttype }}</b></span>{% endif %}
    {% if params.costcenter %}<span>Cost centre <b>{{ params.costcenter }}</b></span>{% endif %}
    <span>Sectors <b>{{ O.sectors|fmt if O.sectors is not none else '—' }}</b></span>
    <span>Projects <b>{{ O.projects|fmt if O.projects is not none else '—' }}</b></span>
    <span>Budget lines <b>{{ O.budget_lines|fmt if O.budget_lines is not none else '—' }}</b></span>
  </div>
  <div class="cv-desc">
    This briefing book presents the consolidated budget utilization position for budget year
    {{ params.year }}{{ ' — ' + params.sector + ' sector' if params.sector else ' across all sectors' }}:
    an executive overview with key indicators, the full register of actuals (supplier invoices and
    goods receipts), open obligations (purchase orders) and open commitments (purchase requisitions),
    closing with observations prepared for management review. All amounts are in AED.
  </div>
  <div class="cv-prep">Prepared by
    <b>Financial Planning and Budgeting</b>
    <i>Finance Department</i>
  </div>
  <div class="cv-date">Generated<b>{{ generated_at }} (Asia/Dubai)</b>{{ report_code }}</div>
  <div class="cv-band2"></div>
</div>

{#- ═══ INDEX ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -#}
<div class="page">
  <div class="toc-h"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
  <table class="toc">
    <tr><td class="no">01</td>
        <td><div class="t">Budget Utilization Overview</div>
            <div class="d">Key indicators for the year, budget composition, utilization by sector and the budget lines under the most pressure.</div></td>
        <td class="n">{{ SEC|length }} sectors &middot; {{ O.budget_lines|fmt if O.budget_lines is not none else '—' }} budget lines</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="no">02</td>
        <td><div class="t">Actuals — Supplier Invoices &amp; Goods Receipts</div>
            <div class="d">Every actual charged to the budget: direct AP invoices (not PO-matched) and GRN goods receipts, with monthly trend and supplier concentration.</div></td>
        <td class="n">{{ AP|length|fmt }} invoices &middot; {{ GRN|length|fmt }} receipt lines</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="no">03</td>
        <td><div class="t">Open Obligations — Purchase Orders</div>
            <div class="d">Funds-reserved purchase-order lines net of goods received: what remains contractually committed to suppliers.</div></td>
        <td class="n">{{ PO|length|fmt }} PO lines</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="no">04</td>
        <td><div class="t">Open Commitments — Purchase Requisitions</div>
            <div class="d">Funds-reserved requisition lines not yet converted to purchase orders: demand in the pipeline.</div></td>
        <td class="n">{{ PR|length|fmt }} PR lines</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="no">05</td>
        <td><div class="t">Observations &amp; Insights</div>
            <div class="d">What the numbers say: pacing, pressure points, concentration and pipeline coverage — with the methodology behind every figure.</div></td>
        <td class="n">&nbsp;</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="foot">{{ meta }}</div>
</div>

{#- ═══ PART 1 — OVERVIEW ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -#}
{% set spent = (O.actual_total or 0) + (O.obligation_po or 0) + (O.commitment_pr or 0) %}
<div class="page">
  <div class="pt-band"><span class="pt-no">01</span><span class="pt-t">Budget Utilization Overview</span>
    <span class="pt-s">Budget year {{ params.year }} &middot; {{ params.sector or 'All sectors' }}</span></div>

  <div class="kpis">
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Approved Budget</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(O.budget) }}</div><div class="k-sub">AED &middot; {{ O.budget_lines|fmt }} lines</div></div>
    <div class="kpi k-act"><div class="k-lbl">Actual — AP</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(O.actual_ap) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ AP|length|fmt }} invoices</div></div>
    <div class="kpi k-act"><div class="k-lbl">Actual — GRN</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(O.actual_grn) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ GRN|length|fmt }} receipt lines</div></div>
    <div class="kpi k-enc"><div class="k-lbl">Open Obligation (PO)</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(O.obligation_po) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ PO|length|fmt }} PO lines</div></div>
    <div class="kpi k-enc"><div class="k-lbl">Open Commitment (PR)</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(O.commitment_pr) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ PR|length|fmt }} PR lines</div></div>
    <div class="kpi {{ 'k-bad' if O.fund_available is not none and O.fund_available < 0 else 'k-ok' }}">
      <div class="k-lbl">Fund Available</div><div class="k-val {{ 'neg' if O.fund_available is not none and O.fund_available < 0 }}">{{ money(O.fund_available) }}</div>
      <div class="k-sub">{{ O.over_budget_lines|fmt }} lines over budget</div></div>
    <div class="kpi {{ 'k-bad' if O.utilization_pct is not none and O.utilization_pct > 100 else '' }}">
      <div class="k-lbl">Utilization</div><div class="k-val">{{ O.utilization_pct|fmt if O.utilization_pct is not none else '—' }}%</div>
      <div class="k-sub">actual + open encumbrance</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="charts">
    <div class="chart" style="flex: 1.2 1 0">
      <div class="ch-t">Budget composition — where the {{ money(O.budget) }} stands</div>
      {% set B = O.budget or 0 %}
      {% if B > 0 %}
      {% set w_ap  = (100 * (O.actual_ap or 0) / B)|round(2) %}
      {% set w_grn = (100 * (O.actual_grn or 0) / B)|round(2) %}
      {% set w_po  = (100 * (O.obligation_po or 0) / B)|round(2) %}
      {% set w_pr  = (100 * (O.commitment_pr or 0) / B)|round(2) %}
      {% set w_fd  = 100 - w_ap - w_grn - w_po - w_pr %}
      <div class="stack">
        <div style="width:{{ [w_ap,0]|max }}%; background: var(--brand);"></div>
        <div style="width:{{ [w_grn,0]|max }}%; background: var(--gold);"></div>
        <div style="width:{{ [w_po,0]|max }}%; background: var(--enc);"></div>
        <div style="width:{{ [w_pr,0]|max }}%; background: #D98E2B;"></div>
        <div style="width:{{ [w_fd,0]|max }}%; background: #DDE7EB;"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="lg">
        <span><i style="background:var(--brand)"></i>AP {{ w_ap }}%</span>
        <span><i style="background:var(--gold)"></i>GRN {{ w_grn }}%</span>
        <span><i style="background:var(--enc)"></i>Open PO {{ w_po }}%</span>
        <span><i style="background:#D98E2B"></i>Open PR {{ w_pr }}%</span>
        <span><i style="background:#DDE7EB"></i>Available {{ w_fd|round(2) }}%</span>
      </div>
      {% else %}<div class="empty">No approved budget in scope.</div>{% endif %}

      <div class="ch-t" style="margin-top:12px">Top sectors by approved budget</div>
      {% set mx = (SEC|map(attribute='budget')|select('number')|max) if SEC else 0 %}
      {% for r in SEC[:8] %}
      <div class="hb-row"><div class="hb-lbl">{{ r.sector }}</div>
        <div class="hb-track"><div class="hb-bar" style="width:{{ (100*(r.budget or 0)/mx)|round(1) if mx else 0 }}%"></div></div>
        <div class="hb-val">{{ money(r.budget) }}</div></div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="chart">
      <div class="ch-t">Utilization by sector — actual + open encumbrance vs budget</div>
      {% for r in (SEC|sort(attribute='utilization_pct', reverse=true))[:14] %}
      {% set u = r.utilization_pct or 0 %}
      <div class="hb-row"><div class="hb-lbl">{{ r.sector }}</div>
        <div class="hb-track"><div class="hb-bar {{ 'bad' if u > 100 else 'warn' if u > 85 else '' }}"
             style="width:{{ [u, 100]|min|round(1) }}%"></div></div>
        <div class="hb-val">{{ u|fmt }}%</div></div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% if not SEC %}<div class="empty">No sector data.</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="foot">Part 1 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

<div class="page">
  <div class="sub-h">1.1 &nbsp; Utilization by sector <small>&mdash; all figures AED</small></div>
  {% if SEC %}
  <table class="data">
    <thead><tr><th>Sector</th><th>Projects</th><th>Budget</th><th>Actual AP</th><th>Actual GRN</th>
      <th>Open PO</th><th>Open PR</th><th>Fund Available</th><th>Utilization %</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in SEC %}
      <tr><td>{{ r.sector }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.projects|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.budget|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.actual_ap|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.actual_grn|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.obligation_po|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.commitment_pr|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num {{ 'neg' if r.fund_available is not none and r.fund_available < 0 }}">{{ r.fund_available|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.utilization_pct|fmt }}</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
    <tfoot><tr><td>Total</td><td class="num">{{ O.projects|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ O.budget|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ O.actual_ap|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ O.actual_grn|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ O.obligation_po|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ O.commitment_pr|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num {{ 'neg' if O.fund_available is not none and O.fund_available < 0 }}">{{ O.fund_available|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ O.utilization_pct|fmt }}</td></tr></tfoot>
  </table>
  {% else %}<div class="empty">No data for the selected criteria.</div>{% endif %}

  <div class="sub-h">1.2 &nbsp; Budget lines under pressure <small>&mdash; lowest remaining funds first (top {{ PRS|length }})</small></div>
  {% if PRS %}
  <table class="data">
    <thead><tr><th>Sector</th><th>Project</th><th>Project Name</th><th>Task</th><th>Expenditure Type</th>
      <th>Budget</th><th>Actual</th><th>Open PO</th><th>Open PR</th><th>Fund Available</th><th>Util %</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in PRS %}
      <tr><td>{{ r.sector or '—' }}</td><td>{{ r.project_number }}</td><td>{{ r.project_name or '—' }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.task_number or '—' }}</td><td>{{ r.expenditure_type or '—' }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.budget|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.actual|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.obligation_po|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.commitment_pr|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num {{ 'neg' if r.fund_available is not none and r.fund_available < 0 }}">{{ r.fund_available|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.utilization_pct|fmt }}</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% else %}<div class="empty">No budget lines in scope.</div>{% endif %}
  <div class="foot">Part 1 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

{#- ═══ PART 2 — ACTUALS ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -#}
{#- monthly trend + supplier concentration computed from the line data -#}
{%- set mo = namespace(d={}) -%}
{%- for r in AP %}{% if r.invoice_date and r.invoice_date.strftime is defined %}
  {%- set k = r.invoice_date.strftime('%Y-%m') %}{% set c = mo.d.get(k, [0, 0]) %}
  {%- set _ = mo.d.update({k: [c[0] + (r.matched_aed or 0), c[1]]}) %}{% endif %}{% endfor -%}
{%- for r in GRN %}{% if r.last_receipt_date and r.last_receipt_date.strftime is defined %}
  {%- set k = r.last_receipt_date.strftime('%Y-%m') %}{% set c = mo.d.get(k, [0, 0]) %}
  {%- set _ = mo.d.update({k: [c[0], c[1] + (r.received_aed or 0)]}) %}{% endif %}{% endfor -%}
{%- set months = mo.d.items()|sort(attribute='0') -%}
{%- set mmax = months|map(attribute='1')|map('max')|max if months else 0 -%}
{%- set sup = namespace(d={}) -%}
{%- for r in AP %}{% set k = r.supplier_name or '(Unknown supplier)' %}
  {%- set _ = sup.d.update({k: sup.d.get(k, 0) + (r.matched_aed or 0)}) %}{% endfor -%}
{%- for r in GRN %}{% set k = r.supplier_name or '(Unknown supplier)' %}
  {%- set _ = sup.d.update({k: sup.d.get(k, 0) + (r.received_aed or 0)}) %}{% endfor -%}
{%- set top_sup = sup.d.items()|sort(attribute='1', reverse=true) -%}
{%- set ap_total = AP|map(attribute='matched_aed')|select('number')|sum -%}
{%- set grn_total = GRN|map(attribute='received_aed')|select('number')|sum -%}
<div class="page">
  <div class="pt-band"><span class="pt-no">02</span><span class="pt-t">Actuals — Supplier Invoices &amp; Goods Receipts</span>
    <span class="pt-s">{{ AP|length|fmt }} AP invoices &middot; {{ GRN|length|fmt }} GRN lines</span></div>

  <div class="kpis">
    <div class="kpi k-act"><div class="k-lbl">Total Actual</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(O.actual_total) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ (100 * (O.actual_total or 0) / O.budget)|round(1) if O.budget else '—' }}% of budget</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">AP Invoices (direct)</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(ap_total) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ AP|length|fmt }} invoices</div></div>
    <div class="kpi k-act"><div class="k-lbl">GRN Receipts</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(grn_total) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ GRN|length|fmt }} receipt lines</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Active Suppliers</div><div class="k-val">{{ sup.d|length|fmt }}</div><div class="k-sub">across AP + GRN</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Top Supplier Share</div>
      <div class="k-val">{{ (100 * top_sup[0][1] / (ap_total + grn_total))|round(1) if top_sup and (ap_total + grn_total) else '—' }}%</div>
      <div class="k-sub">{{ top_sup[0][0]|string|truncate(26) if top_sup else '—' }}</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="charts">
    <div class="chart" style="flex: 1.25 1 0">
      <div class="ch-t">Monthly actuals — <i style="color:var(--brand)">AP</i> vs <i style="color:var(--gold)">GRN</i> (AED)</div>
      {% if months %}
      <div class="cols">
        {% for m, v in months %}
        <div style="flex:1 1 0">
          <div class="col-g">
            <div class="col-ap" style="height:{{ (100 * v[0] / mmax)|round(1) if mmax else 0 }}px"></div>
            <div class="col-grn" style="height:{{ (100 * v[1] / mmax)|round(1) if mmax else 0 }}px"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lbl">{{ m[5:] }}/{{ m[2:4] }}</div>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% else %}<div class="empty">No dated actuals in scope.</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="chart">
      <div class="ch-t">Top 10 suppliers by actual spend</div>
      {% for name, amt in top_sup[:10] %}
      <div class="hb-row"><div class="hb-lbl">{{ name|string|truncate(30) }}</div>
        <div class="hb-track"><div class="hb-bar gold" style="width:{{ (100 * amt / top_sup[0][1])|round(1) if top_sup[0][1] else 0 }}%"></div></div>
        <div class="hb-val">{{ money(amt) }}</div></div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% if not top_sup %}<div class="empty">No supplier activity.</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="foot">Part 2 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

<div class="page">
  <div class="sub-h">2.1 &nbsp; AP invoices charged directly to the budget <small>&mdash; {{ AP|length|fmt }} invoices, not PO-matched</small></div>
  {% if AP %}
  <table class="data">
    <thead><tr><th>Project</th><th>Project Name</th><th>Task</th><th>Expenditure Type</th>
      <th>Invoice #</th><th>Invoice Date</th><th>Supplier</th><th>Curr</th>
      <th>Charged AED</th><th>Payment</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in AP %}
      <tr><td>{{ r.project_number }}</td><td>{{ (r.project_name or '—')|string|truncate(38) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.task_number or '—' }}</td><td>{{ (r.expenditure_type or '—')|string|truncate(30) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.invoice_number }}</td><td>{{ dt(r.invoice_date) }}</td>
        <td>{{ (r.supplier_name or '—')|string|truncate(34) }}</td><td>{{ r.currency or 'AED' }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.matched_aed|fmt }}</td>
        <td><span class="pill {{ 'paid' if r.payment_status == 'Paid' else 'part' if r.payment_status == 'Partially Paid' else 'unp' }}">{{ r.payment_status }}</span></td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
    <tfoot><tr><td colspan="8">Total — AP invoices</td><td class="num">{{ ap_total|fmt }}</td><td></td></tr></tfoot>
  </table>
  {% else %}<div class="empty">No direct AP invoices for the selected criteria.</div>{% endif %}
  <div class="foot">Part 2.1 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

<div class="page">
  <div class="sub-h">2.2 &nbsp; Goods receipts (GRN) <small>&mdash; {{ GRN|length|fmt }} receipt lines by purchase-order distribution</small></div>
  {% if GRN %}
  <table class="data">
    <thead><tr><th>Project</th><th>Project Name</th><th>Task</th><th>Expenditure Type</th>
      <th>PO #</th><th>Line</th><th>Supplier</th><th>Last Receipt</th><th>Receipts</th>
      <th>Received AED</th><th>Invoiced AED</th><th>Uninvoiced AED</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in GRN %}
      <tr><td>{{ r.project_number }}</td><td>{{ (r.project_name or '—')|string|truncate(34) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.task_number or '—' }}</td><td>{{ (r.expenditure_type or '—')|string|truncate(28) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.po_number }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.po_line }}</td>
        <td>{{ (r.supplier_name or '—')|string|truncate(30) }}</td><td>{{ dt(r.last_receipt_date) }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.receipt_lines|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.received_aed|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.invoiced_aed|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.uninvoiced_aed|fmt }}</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
    <tfoot><tr><td colspan="9">Total — goods receipts</td>
      <td class="num">{{ grn_total|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ GRN|map(attribute='invoiced_aed')|select('number')|sum|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ GRN|map(attribute='uninvoiced_aed')|select('number')|sum|fmt }}</td></tr></tfoot>
  </table>
  {% else %}<div class="empty">No goods receipts for the selected criteria.</div>{% endif %}
  <div class="foot">Part 2.2 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

{#- ═══ PART 3 — OPEN OBLIGATIONS ═══════════════════════════════════════ -#}
{%- set po_sup = namespace(d={}) -%}
{%- for r in PO %}{% set k = r.supplier_name or '(Unknown supplier)' %}
  {%- set _ = po_sup.d.update({k: po_sup.d.get(k, 0) + (r.open_aed or 0)}) %}{% endfor -%}
{%- set po_top = po_sup.d.items()|sort(attribute='1', reverse=true) -%}
{%- set po_total = PO|map(attribute='open_aed')|select('number')|sum -%}
<div class="page">
  <div class="pt-band"><span class="pt-no">03</span><span class="pt-t">Open Obligations — Purchase Orders</span>
    <span class="pt-s">{{ PO|length|fmt }} funds-reserved PO lines, net of goods received</span></div>

  <div class="kpis">
    <div class="kpi k-enc"><div class="k-lbl">Open Obligation</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(po_total) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ (100 * po_total / O.budget)|round(1) if O.budget else '—' }}% of budget</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">PO Lines</div><div class="k-val">{{ PO|length|fmt }}</div><div class="k-sub">Reserved / Partially Liquidated</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Suppliers</div><div class="k-val">{{ po_sup.d|length|fmt }}</div><div class="k-sub">holding open orders</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Largest Single Line</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(PO[0].open_aed) if PO else '—' }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ (PO[0].supplier_name or '—')|string|truncate(26) if PO else '' }}</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="charts">
    <div class="chart">
      <div class="ch-t">Top 10 suppliers by open obligation</div>
      {% for name, amt in po_top[:10] %}
      <div class="hb-row"><div class="hb-lbl">{{ name|string|truncate(30) }}</div>
        <div class="hb-track"><div class="hb-bar warn" style="width:{{ (100 * amt / po_top[0][1])|round(1) if po_top[0][1] else 0 }}%"></div></div>
        <div class="hb-val">{{ money(amt) }}</div></div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% if not po_top %}<div class="empty">No open purchase orders.</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="chart">
      <div class="ch-t">Largest open PO lines</div>
      {% for r in PO[:10] %}
      <div class="hb-row"><div class="hb-lbl">{{ r.po_number }}/{{ r.po_line }} &middot; {{ (r.supplier_name or '')|string|truncate(18) }}</div>
        <div class="hb-track"><div class="hb-bar" style="width:{{ (100 * (r.open_aed or 0) / PO[0].open_aed)|round(1) if PO[0].open_aed else 0 }}%"></div></div>
        <div class="hb-val">{{ money(r.open_aed) }}</div></div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% if not PO %}<div class="empty">No open purchase orders.</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="foot">Part 3 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

<div class="page">
  <div class="sub-h">3.1 &nbsp; Open purchase-order lines <small>&mdash; ordered by open amount, GRN-netted</small></div>
  {% if PO %}
  <table class="data">
    <thead><tr><th>Project</th><th>Project Name</th><th>Task</th><th>Expenditure Type</th>
      <th>PO #</th><th>Line</th><th>Budget Date</th><th>Supplier</th><th>Funds Status</th>
      <th>Line AED</th><th>Received AED</th><th>Open AED</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in PO %}
      <tr><td>{{ r.project_number }}</td><td>{{ (r.project_name or '—')|string|truncate(32) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.task_number or '—' }}</td><td>{{ (r.expenditure_type or '—')|string|truncate(28) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.po_number }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.po_line }}</td><td>{{ dt(r.budget_date) }}</td>
        <td>{{ (r.supplier_name or '—')|string|truncate(30) }}</td><td>{{ r.funds_status }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.line_aed|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.received_aed|fmt }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.open_aed|fmt }}</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
    <tfoot><tr><td colspan="9">Total — open obligations</td>
      <td class="num">{{ PO|map(attribute='line_aed')|select('number')|sum|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ PO|map(attribute='received_aed')|select('number')|sum|fmt }}</td>
      <td class="num">{{ po_total|fmt }}</td></tr></tfoot>
  </table>
  {% else %}<div class="empty">No open purchase orders for the selected criteria.</div>{% endif %}
  <div class="foot">Part 3.1 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

{#- ═══ PART 4 — OPEN COMMITMENTS ═══════════════════════════════════════ -#}
{%- set pr_total = PR|map(attribute='amount_aed')|select('number')|sum -%}
<div class="page">
  <div class="pt-band"><span class="pt-no">04</span><span class="pt-t">Open Commitments — Purchase Requisitions</span>
    <span class="pt-s">{{ PR|length|fmt }} funds-reserved PR lines awaiting purchase orders</span></div>

  <div class="kpis">
    <div class="kpi k-enc"><div class="k-lbl">Open Commitment</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(pr_total) }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ (100 * pr_total / O.budget)|round(1) if O.budget else '—' }}% of budget</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">PR Lines</div><div class="k-val">{{ PR|length|fmt }}</div><div class="k-sub">funds status Reserved</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Largest Single Line</div><div class="k-val">{{ money(PR[0].amount_aed) if PR else '—' }}</div><div class="k-sub">{{ (PR[0].pr_number or '')|string|truncate(24) if PR else '' }}</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="k-lbl">Pipeline (PO + PR)</div><div class="k-val">{{ money((O.obligation_po or 0) + (O.commitment_pr or 0)) }}</div><div class="k-sub">total open encumbrance</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="charts">
    <div class="chart">
      <div class="ch-t">Largest open requisition lines</div>
      {% for r in PR[:12] %}
      <div class="hb-row"><div class="hb-lbl">{{ r.pr_number }} &middot; {{ (r.project_number or '')|string|truncate(14) }}</div>
        <div class="hb-track"><div class="hb-bar warn" style="width:{{ (100 * (r.amount_aed or 0) / PR[0].amount_aed)|round(1) if PR[0].amount_aed else 0 }}%"></div></div>
        <div class="hb-val">{{ money(r.amount_aed) }}</div></div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% if not PR %}<div class="empty">No open requisitions.</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="foot">Part 4 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

<div class="page">
  <div class="sub-h">4.1 &nbsp; Open purchase-requisition lines <small>&mdash; ordered by amount</small></div>
  {% if PR %}
  <table class="data">
    <thead><tr><th>Project</th><th>Project Name</th><th>Task</th><th>Expenditure Type</th>
      <th>PR #</th><th>Description</th><th>Budget Date</th><th>Curr</th>
      <th>Amount</th><th>Amount AED</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in PR %}
      <tr><td>{{ r.project_number }}</td><td>{{ (r.project_name or '—')|string|truncate(30) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.task_number or '—' }}</td><td>{{ (r.expenditure_type or '—')|string|truncate(26) }}</td>
        <td>{{ r.pr_number }}</td><td>{{ (r.description or '—')|string|truncate(46) }}</td>
        <td>{{ dt(r.budget_date) }}</td><td>{{ r.currency or 'AED' }}</td>
        <td class="num">{{ r.distribution_amount|fmt }}</td><td class="num">{{ r.amount_aed|fmt }}</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
    <tfoot><tr><td colspan="9">Total — open commitments</td><td class="num">{{ pr_total|fmt }}</td></tr></tfoot>
  </table>
  {% else %}<div class="empty">No open requisitions for the selected criteria.</div>{% endif %}
  <div class="foot">Part 4.1 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot; Amounts in AED</div>
</div>

{#- ═══ PART 5 — INSIGHTS ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -#}
{%- set gy = generated_at[:4]|int -%}
{%- set gm = generated_at[5:7]|int -%}
{%- set yr = params.year|int -%}
{%- set elapsed = 100 if yr < gy else ((100 * gm / 12)|round(0)|int if yr == gy else 0) -%}
{%- set actual_pct = (100 * (O.actual_total or 0) / O.budget)|round(1) if O.budget else 0 -%}
{%- set oldest_po = (PO|selectattr('budget_date')|sort(attribute='budget_date')|list|first) if PO else none -%}
<div class="page">
  <div class="pt-band"><span class="pt-no">05</span><span class="pt-t">Observations &amp; Insights</span>
    <span class="pt-s">prepared for management review</span></div>

  <div class="ins"><div class="i-t">Pacing — spend vs time</div>
    <div class="i-b">With <b>{{ elapsed }}%</b> of budget year {{ params.year }} elapsed, committed
    utilization stands at <b>{{ O.utilization_pct|fmt }}%</b> ({{ money(spent) }} of {{ money(O.budget) }})
    while cash-realised actuals alone are <b>{{ actual_pct }}%</b>.
    {% if O.utilization_pct is not none %}{% if O.utilization_pct > elapsed + 10 %}Utilization is running
    <b>ahead of the calendar</b> — remaining funds may be exhausted before year-end at the current pace.
    {% elif O.utilization_pct < elapsed - 25 %}Utilization is running <b>well behind the calendar</b> —
    review whether planned initiatives are delayed or budgets can be reallocated.
    {% else %}Utilization is broadly <b>in line with the calendar</b>.{% endif %}{% endif %}</div></div>

  <div class="ins"><div class="i-t">Budget pressure</div>
    <div class="i-b"><b>{{ O.over_budget_lines|fmt }}</b> budget line(s) are over budget (negative fund
    available){% if PRS %}; the tightest is <b>{{ PRS[0].project_number }}</b>
    {{ '· ' + PRS[0].expenditure_type if PRS[0].expenditure_type }} at
    <b class="{{ 'neg' if PRS[0].fund_available < 0 }}">{{ PRS[0].fund_available|fmt }} AED</b> remaining
    ({{ PRS[0].utilization_pct|fmt }}% utilized){% endif %}. Part 1.2 lists the {{ PRS|length }} lines
    with the least headroom.</div></div>

  <div class="ins"><div class="i-t">Supplier concentration</div>
    <div class="i-b">{% if top_sup %}The top supplier, <b>{{ top_sup[0][0] }}</b>, accounts for
    <b>{{ (100 * top_sup[0][1] / (ap_total + grn_total))|round(1) if (ap_total + grn_total) else 0 }}%</b>
    of all actuals ({{ money(top_sup[0][1]) }}); the top five suppliers hold
    <b>{{ (100 * (top_sup[:5]|map(attribute='1')|sum) / (ap_total + grn_total))|round(1) if (ap_total + grn_total) else 0 }}%</b>
    across {{ sup.d|length }} active suppliers.{% else %}No supplier activity recorded in scope.{% endif %}</div></div>

  <div class="ins"><div class="i-t">Delivery pipeline</div>
    <div class="i-b">Open encumbrances total <b>{{ money((O.obligation_po or 0) + (O.commitment_pr or 0)) }}</b> —
    {{ money(O.obligation_po) }} contractually obligated on {{ PO|length|fmt }} PO lines plus
    {{ money(O.commitment_pr) }} requested on {{ PR|length|fmt }} PR lines. If everything open is
    delivered and invoiced, utilization reaches the committed <b>{{ O.utilization_pct|fmt }}%</b>.
    {% if oldest_po %}The oldest open PO line dates to <b>{{ dt(oldest_po.budget_date) }}</b>
    ({{ oldest_po.po_number }}, {{ (oldest_po.supplier_name or '—')|string|truncate(34) }}) — aged open orders
    are candidates for close-out to release funds.{% endif %}</div></div>

  <div class="ins"><div class="i-t">Uninvoiced deliveries</div>
    <div class="i-b">{% set uninv = GRN|map(attribute='uninvoiced_aed')|select('number')|sum %}
    Goods worth <b>{{ money(uninv) }}</b> have been received but not yet invoiced by suppliers
    (Part 2.2, Uninvoiced AED) — an accrual to anticipate in upcoming AP volumes.</div></div>

  <div class="meth">
    <h4>Methodology</h4>
    <div>
      <b>Actual — AP</b>: validated supplier-invoice distributions charged directly to projects (not PO-matched), AED functional amounts. &nbsp;
      <b>Actual — GRN</b>: goods-receipt ledger amounts per purchase-order distribution. &nbsp;
      <b>Open Obligation (PO)</b>: purchase-order distributions with funds status Reserved / Partially Liquidated, net of goods received; finally-closed orders excluded. &nbsp;
      <b>Open Commitment (PR)</b>: requisition distributions with funds status Reserved, AED via the corporate rate snapshot. &nbsp;
      <b>Fund Available</b> = Budget &minus; Actuals &minus; Open PO &minus; Open PR. &nbsp;
      <b>Utilization %</b> = (Actuals + Open PO + Open PR) &divide; Budget.
      Source: i-Finance GL Budget Utilization layer (prod.dct_budget_utilization_v and its detail views), Fusion-loaded data as of the generation time.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="foot">Part 5 &middot; Budget Utilization Briefing Book &middot; {{ params.year }} &middot;
    Generated {{ generated_at }} (Asia/Dubai) &middot; {{ report_code }} &middot;
    Prepared by Financial Planning and Budgeting — Finance Department</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
